'''bracer''' (''plural'' bracers)
# That which [[brace]]s, [[bind]]s, or makes [[firm]]; a [[band]] or [[bandage]].
# A [[cover]]ing to [[protect]] the [[arm]] of the [[bowman]] from the [[vibration]] of the [[string]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1786''': To [[prevent]] the [[bow string]] from [[hang]]ing on the left [[arm]], it is covered with a piece of [[smooth]] [[leather]], [[fasten]]ed on the outside of the arm, this is called a [[bracer]]. &mdash; Francis Grose, ''A Treatise on Ancient Armour and Weapons'', page 34.
# (''Armor'') [[Category:Armor]] [[Armor]] for the [[forearm]]; a [[brassart]].
# A [[medicine]], as an [[astringent]] or a [[tonic]], which gives [[tension]] or [[tone]] to any part of the [[body]].